AUDIO: 'My goodness - this is insanity. Earlier, when running an experiment with 25 ChatGPT AI agents playing a video game together in a simulated town, absolutely magical things happened. What happened?'

[00:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Well, they planned their days, formed relationships, invited each other to parties which they also organized, and more. I absolutely loved this paper, and my goodness, here is an even crazier one. It has an insane idea.'

[00:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If these AI assistants can have their own identities, motivations and they can converse in full natural language, why not ask them to form a company to develop video games! But, how does this even work?'

[00:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Well, each of them get assigned an identity, for instance, we can say that you are going to be the CEO, little AI, and you are going to be the CTO. Then, they can make decisions together, and perhaps even more importantly, they reflect'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'upon these decisions later and evaluate whether they have done well. So, what did they do? Look!'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
